Just to share where my heart is….I truly hope to reflect on these early days fondly as the “shitshow good ol’ days” of what we survived and built together. 

I want to build something I believe in. And I believe in what Solar brings to the world. I know what fake passion in a product feels like, sadly. But that ceases to exist for me in Solar. 

Without hesitation, I believe we are far more suitable than any company to bring good solar outcomes to the world. 

And a $350k base wouldn’t sway me. In a sick way, I like the battle scars, I want the bloody field of battle, I want that team victory, not victories by individual commissions.
